ing array of domestic and foreign policy challenges. Not surprisingly, then, the Obama administration has been the focus of intense scrutiny by scholars, the press, and the public, and rarely has the tone of political discourse been more polarized and emotionally charged. In this book a distinguished group of scholars offers an objective and timely examination of the Obama administration; Obama's character, leadership style, and rhetoric; and his domestic, foreign, and national security policies. Engaging, lively, and highly readable, each essay offers important insight into this historic president and presidency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPolitics and Law : Presidency, The. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / Executive Branch.2bisacsh1 aBrattebo, Douglas M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrattebo, Douglas M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCovarrubias, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCovarrubias, Jack, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCutler, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaynes, Byron W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDodds, Graham G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFisher, Louis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Matthew N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGusmano, Michael K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolder, R. Ward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKao, De-Yuan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLansford, Tom, e